Einstein equations
\layout Standard


\series bold 
Einstein equations in almost flat space
\layout Standard

Compute 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{Ric}_{\mu\nu}$
\end_inset 

 to first order in Newtonian gauge:
\begin_inset Formula \[
\begin{cases}
h_{00}=2\Phi;\quad h_{0j}=S_{j};\quad S_{j}{}^{,j}=0\\
h_{ij}=2\Psi\delta_{ij}+t_{ij},\quad t_{aa}=0,\; t_{ij}{}^{,j}=0\end{cases}\]

\end_inset 

Need to compute 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
\textrm{Ric}_{\mu\nu} & =\frac{\left(\textrm{Tr}h\right)_{,\mu\nu}+\square h_{\mu\nu}-\partial_{\mu}\left(\textrm{div}h\right)_{\nu}-\partial_{\nu}\left(\textrm{div}h\right)_{\mu}}{2}\\
\textrm{Tr}\, h & =2\Phi-6\Psi\\
\left(\textrm{div}h\right)_{0} & =g^{\mu\nu}h_{0\mu,\nu}=h_{00,0}-h_{0j,j}=2\dot{\Phi}\\
\left(\textrm{div}h\right)_{j} & =h_{j0,0}-h_{ji,i}=\dot{S}_{j}-2\Psi_{,j}\end{align*}

\end_inset 


\layout Standard

Hence (in the SVT decomposition):
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
\textrm{Ric}_{00} & =-3\ddot{\Psi}-\Delta\Phi,\quad\textrm{Ric}_{0j}=-2\dot{\Psi}_{,j}-\frac{1}{2}\Delta S_{j}\\
\textrm{Ric}_{ij} & =\left(\Phi-\Psi\right)_{,ij}+\frac{1}{2}\square t_{ij}+\delta_{ij}\square\Psi-\frac{1}{2}\left(\dot{S}_{j,i}+\dot{S}_{i,j}\right)\\
R & =\textrm{Ric}_{00}-\textrm{Ric}_{jj}=-6\ddot{\Psi}-2\Delta\Phi+4\Delta\Psi\end{align*}

\end_inset 


\layout Standard

Need to decompose the EMT in 3+1/SVT:
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
T_{0j} & =\alpha_{,j}+\beta_{j};\qquad\beta_{j}{}^{,j}=0\\
T_{ij} & =\mu\delta_{ij}+\lambda_{,ij}+\sigma_{i,j}+\sigma_{j,i}+q_{ij}\\
\sigma_{j}{}^{,j} & =0,\quad q_{jj}=0,\quad q_{ij}{}^{,j}=0\end{align*}

\end_inset 

 
\layout Slide

Explicit solutions
\layout Standard


\series bold 
Explicit solutions
\layout Standard

Explicit expressions for 3+1/SVT components:
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
\alpha=\frac{1}{\Delta}T_{0i,i}\quad\lambda & =\frac{1}{\Delta}\left[\frac{3}{2}\frac{1}{\Delta}T_{ik,ik}-\frac{1}{2}T_{ii}\right]\\
\mu=\frac{1}{2}\left[T_{ii}-\frac{1}{\Delta}T_{ik,ik}\right]\quad\sigma_{j} & =\frac{1}{\Delta}\left[T_{ji,i}-\left(\frac{1}{\Delta}T_{ik,ik}\right)_{,j}\right]\end{align*}

\end_inset 

 Einstein equations in 3+1 decomposition are
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
-2\Delta\Psi & =-8\pi GT_{00}\\
-2\dot{\Psi}_{,j}-\frac{1}{2}\Delta S_{j} & =-8\pi G\left(\alpha_{,j}+\beta_{j}\right)\\
\left(\Phi-\Psi\right)_{,ij}+\frac{1}{2}\square t_{ij} & -\frac{1}{2}\left(\dot{S}_{j,i}+\dot{S}_{i,j}\right)\\
-\left[2\ddot{\Psi}+\Delta\left(\Phi-\Psi\right)\right]\delta_{ij} & =-8\pi G(\mu\delta_{ij}+\lambda_{,ij}\\
 & +\sigma_{i,j}+\sigma_{j,i}+q_{ij})\end{align*}

\end_inset 

Explicit solution using SVT theorem 1:
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
\Psi & =\frac{1}{\Delta}4\pi GT_{00},\quad\Phi-\Psi=-8\pi G\lambda,\\
S_{j} & =\frac{1}{\Delta}16\pi G\beta_{j},\quad t_{ij}=\frac{1}{\square}16\pi Gq_{ij}\end{align*}

\end_inset 

Remarks: 1.
 Other equations are consequences of 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{ij}{}^{,j}=0$
\end_inset 

, do not need to solve them!
\newline 
2.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\Phi,\Psi,S_{j}$
\end_inset 

 are constrained and not free d.o.f.
\newline 
3.
 A free wave solution can be added to 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{ij}$
\end_inset 

 (this gives 2 vacuum d.o.f.)
\newline 
4.
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{\mu\nu}=\left(\rho+p\right)u_{\mu}u_{\nu}-pg_{\mu\nu}$
\end_inset 

 we have 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha=0$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=0$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu=p$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{j}=\beta_{j}=0$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{ij}=0$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{00}=\rho+p$
\end_inset 


