 Perturbations of gravity and matter in FRW spacetime 
\newline 

\series default 
(see 
\noun on 
Mukhanov
\noun default 
 2005, chapters 7 and 8)
\layout Standard

Perturbations due to a single, ideal comoving fluid (if 
\emph on 
one
\emph default 
 matter component dominates 
\emph on 
and 
\emph default 
if vector perturbations are absent, e.g.\SpecialChar ~
scalar field/dust/radiation but no
 cosmic strings):
\begin_inset Formula \[
T_{\mu\nu}=\left(\rho+p\right)u_{\mu}u_{\nu}-pg_{\mu\nu}\]

\end_inset 

In 
\emph on 
flat
\emph default 
 spacetime it follows that 
\begin_inset Formula $\Phi=\Psi$
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{j}=0$
\end_inset 

, so the perturbed metric is simply
\begin_inset Formula \[
\tilde{g}_{\mu\nu}=\left(\begin{array}{cc}
1+2\Phi & 0\\
0 & -\delta_{ij}+2\Phi\delta_{ij}+t_{ij}\end{array}\right),\; u^{\mu}=\left(\begin{array}{c}
1\\
0\\
0\\
0\end{array}\right)\]

\end_inset 

To pass to FRW spacetime, note that any FRW spacetime is conformally flat:
\begin_inset Formula \[
g=d\tilde{t}^{2}-\tilde{a}^{2}(\tilde{t})d\mathbf{x}^{2}=a^{2}(t)\left[dt^{2}-d\mathbf{x}^{2}\right]\]

\end_inset 

 Note: 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset 

 is the 
\series bold 
conformal time
\series default 
, 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{t}$
\end_inset 

 is the proper time, 
\begin_inset Formula $t=\int\frac{d\tilde{t}}{\tilde{a}(\tilde{t})}$
\end_inset 


\newline 
Example: de Sitter, 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{a}(\tilde{t})=e^{H\tilde{t}}$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $t=-H^{-1}e^{-H\tilde{t}}$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $a(t)=\left|Ht\right|^{-1}$
\end_inset 

 
\newline 
Note that 
\begin_inset Formula $-\infty<t<0$
\end_inset 

 for de Sitter; 
\begin_inset Formula $t\rightarrow0$
\end_inset 

 is 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

late times
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 


\newline 
In matter-dominated FRW, 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{a}(\tilde{t})\propto\tilde{t}^{p}$
\end_inset 

 where usually 
\begin_inset Formula $0<p<1$
\end_inset 

 and so 
\begin_inset Formula $0<t<\infty$
\end_inset 


